docs.abstract: In his State of the Union address on Tuesday, the president is expected to announce a plan that calls for an expanded effort to prevent the virus that causes AIDS.
docs.snippet: In his State of the Union address on Tuesday, the president is expected to announce a plan that calls for an expanded effort to prevent the virus that causes AIDS.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump is expected to announce in his State of the Union speech a national commitment to end transmission of the virus that causes AIDS, with a goal of stopping its spread in this country by 2030.

headline.main: Trump Expected to Announce Plan to Stop Spread of H.I.V. in the U.S. by 2030
headline.print_headline: Trump Plans New Push To Prevent H.I.V. Spread

byline.original: By Robert Pear and Katie Rogers

docs.abstract: Representative Dave Brat’s stunning victory in 2014 showed the power of insurgency. But he is facing an uprising of his own among Democratic women in his Virginia congressional district.
docs.snippet: Representative Dave Brat’s stunning victory in 2014 showed the power of insurgency. But he is facing an uprising of his own among Democratic women in his Virginia congressional district.
docs.lead_paragraph: MIDLOTHIAN, Va. — The Liberal Women of Chesterfield County did not exist when Representative Dave Brat, propelled by Tea Party-infused energy, shocked the Republican establishment in 2014 and defeated the House majority leader, Eric Cantor, in a primary triumph here that presaged even greater political upheaval two years later.

headline.main: In Virginia, Women Form an Insurgency to Try to Topple Republican Dave Brat
headline.print_headline: Republican, Elected as an Insurgent, Faces an Uprising Led by Women

docs.abstract: During the contentious meeting, the president made his case for a border wall and rejected Democrats’ proposals for reopening the government while the two sides ironed out their differences.
docs.snippet: During the contentious meeting, the president made his case for a border wall and rejected Democrats’ proposals for reopening the government while the two sides ironed out their differences.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and Democratic congressional leaders dug in Wednesday for a lengthy partial shutdown in a newly divided government after a White House meeting — the first in 22 days — could not break an impasse over Mr. Trump’s demands for billions of dollars for a border wall.

headline.main: Trump and Democrats Dig In After Talks to Reopen Government Go Nowhere
headline.print_headline: Stances Harden In Talks to Solve Shutdown Crisis

byline.original: By Julie Hirschfeld Davis and Michael Tackett

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump wanted to talk. He initially invited A. G. Sulzberger, the publisher of The New York Times, to an off-the-record dinner. Mr. Sulzberger countered with a request for an on-the-record interview that included Times reporters. The White House accepted.

headline.main: 5 Takeaways From The Times’s Interview With President Trump

docs.abstract: More than 200 members of Congress are supporting a bill that would increase payroll taxes to shore up Social Security and increase benefits for retirees.
docs.snippet: More than 200 members of Congress are supporting a bill that would increase payroll taxes to shore up Social Security and increase benefits for retirees.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After years of Republican-led debate over how to pare back Social Security’s rising costs, Democrats are flipping the script with an ambitious plan to expand the New Deal-era social insurance program while making gradual changes to keep it solvent for the rest of the century.

headline.main: Democrats Push Plan to Increase Social Security Benefits and Solvency
headline.print_headline: Democrats Push First Major Social Security Expansion Since 1972

docs.abstract: The G.A.O. found that four trips in 2017 cost taxpayers $13.6 million. Officials say the tab is probably higher, but offered only a snapshot because the White House didn’t provide more information.
docs.snippet: The G.A.O. found that four trips in 2017 cost taxpayers $13.6 million. Officials say the tab is probably higher, but offered only a snapshot because the White House didn’t provide more information.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Government Accountability Office set out in 2017 to calculate the total cost to taxpayers of President Trump’s trips to Mar-a-Lago, his resort in Palm Beach, Fla., but said in a report issued on Tuesday that it could come up with only a snapshot of the expenses because the Trump administration did not respond to requests for more information.

headline.main: How Much Are Trump’s Mar-a-Lago Trips? Watchdog Agency Struggles to Find Out
headline.print_headline: Trump Visits Mar-a-Lago Four Times, At What Cost?

docs.abstract: After a cancellation and before another potential funding lapse, Congress was finally ready to hear what, exactly, the state of the union is.
docs.snippet: After a cancellation and before another potential funding lapse, Congress was finally ready to hear what, exactly, the state of the union is.
docs.lead_paragraph: They leapt to their feet, dozens of Democratic women, jubilant in their hues of suffragist white as they hugged and grasped hands. For most of the night, they had frequently been stone-faced, often reluctant to applaud President Trump’s declarations.

headline.main: Before the State of the Union, a Day of Anticipation and Preparation
headline.print_headline: At Capitol, a Day of Anticipation and Applause

docs.abstract: House Democratic women wore white to the State of the Union address to celebrate their historic numbers and to protest President Trump. He surprised them.
docs.snippet: House Democratic women wore white to the State of the Union address to celebrate their historic numbers and to protest President Trump. He surprised them.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — There was a striking island of white in the audience for President Trump’s State of the Union address, with House Democratic women — many of them dressed in the color in a nod to the American suffragist movement — sitting together in the packed chamber, in a celebration of their historic numbers in Congress and also as a protest to Mr. Trump’s policies.

headline.main: The Women in White: Praise From Trump, and Chants of ‘U.S.A.!’
headline.print_headline: Dressed for Protest, but Not Without Successes to Cheer

docs.abstract: The story of a modification to the Boeing 737’s flight control system shows how competitive pressures and technological complexity can affect airliner safety.
docs.snippet: The story of a modification to the Boeing 737’s flight control system shows how competitive pressures and technological complexity can affect airliner safety.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the brutally competitive jetliner business, the announcement in late 2010 that Airbus would introduce a more fuel-efficient version of its best-selling A320 amounted to a frontal assault on its archrival Boeing’s workhorse 737.

headline.main: After a Lion Air 737 Max Crashed in October, Questions About the Plane Arose
headline.print_headline: Jet’s Software Was Updated. Pilots Weren’t.
